5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 569, L.D. 1375, “Resolve, to Establish a
10 Working Group to Address Regulatory Barriers to Housing Construction”
11 Amend the resolve by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. Working group. Resolved: That the Office of Policy, Innovation and the
13 Future, referred to in this resolve as "the office," shall within existing resources convene a
14 working group to examine and recommend solutions for regulatory barriers to housing
15 construction in this State. The working group must be administered by the office and must
16 include, but is not limited to, individuals and representatives of organizations with building
17 and engineering expertise and state and local building code experience. The office shall
18 designate a chair of the working group.'
19 Amend the resolve in section 2 in the first line (page 1, line 7 in L.D.) by striking out
20 the following: "program" and inserting the following: 'office'
21 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
22 section number to read consecutively.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This amendment assigns responsibility for the working group to the Office of Policy,
2255 Innovation and the Future. The amendment requires the office to complete the work within
2266 existing resources and assign a chair of the working group.
2277 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2288 (See attached)
